******
[1] Kyrgyzstan
Date: Mon 7 Feb 2015
Source: 24.kg News Agency [edited]
http://www.eng.24.kg/zdorovye/178351-news24.html


2 fatal cases of rabies have been recorded in Kyrgyzstan in 2015. This was reported to the 24.kg News Agency by the press service of the Disease Prevention and Sanitary Inspection Department.

According to them, the last case was registered in Kara-Suu district of Osh region, [where] on 1 Nov 2015, a rabies- infected dog bit animals and local residents in the village of Uchar. "As a result, a 2-year-old girl died in a hospital 10 days later. The animal has bitten 4 children, who received treatment. Their condition is stable," the press service reported.

They added that in mid-2015, the death of a 72-year-old man was recorded in Kara-Buura district of Talas region. Having been bitten by a jackal, he turned for medical help only after clinical manifestations of the disease, when the doctors were not able to provide the necessary aid.

At least 4 people have died of the infection in the Kyrgyz Republic during the last 3 years.

[Byline: Nurzhamal Ganeyva]

--
Communicated by:
